ibilities:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ensures physical security of the servers where the application is hosted."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Provides a secure networking infrastructure."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Customer Responsibilities:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Configures IAM roles to prevent unauthorized access."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Encrypts customer payment data stored in Amazon S3."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Updates the application code to fix vulnerabilities."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"summary"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Summary"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The AWS Shared Responsibility Model is a key framework for cloud security, making it clear where AWS’s responsibilities end and where the customer’s begin. By embracing this model, businesses can take full advantage of AWS’s secure infrastructure while safeguarding their workloads and data."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Remember: "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"AWS secures the cloud; you secure what you put in the cloud."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Understanding the shared responsibility model is the first step toward building secure, reliable, and compliant cloud solutions. So, the next time you deploy workloads in AWS, take a moment to review your responsibilities and ensure everything is c